I think that misses the point.  Otherwise you can add Fire and Fury and League of Shadows to that list, because (oh dear god), Caparelli wasn't the original owner, but the original owner gave the character to Bako, who was his real life friend.  Norok isn't the original Norok, was given to a real life friend of Ermok.  Adelaide isn't the original Adelaide (real life friend of Tallonar and myself), was given to Tallonar, and (oh dear god) he even gave him a couple of dollars for it too!<br>
<br>
I don't believe these examples above violate the spirit of the EULA, and I don't think there's anything wrong with them.<br>
<br>
