<br>
Bob has an EQ character that is poor.  However, Bob himself has a bit of cash to spare from working overtime last weekend.  He uses that RL cash to purchase plat on his server.<br>
<br>
Pete also has a character that is poor.  However, Pete can draw very beautiful siggies, and he sells siggies for in-game plat.<br>
<br>
I am not trying to be obnoxious.  I am trying to understand.  Why is the first example frowned upon, and the second example not only accepted but encouraged?  What, honestly, is the difference?  Both Bob and Pete traded RL goods (in one instance cash, in the other, artwork) for in-game pp/items.  If the second is ok, then would a person purchasing an account using their artwork as trade be ok as well?  And if not, why not?<br>
<br>
Again, I'm not trying to be obtuse here ... I am trying to understand the logic, if there is any, in how/why both situations are viewed/handled by the community. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://carim.home.mindspring.com/thenidge1.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
